President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation designating July 17 through July 23, 2016, as Captive Nations Week. During this week, the United States recognizes the inherent dignity of all people and renews its support for those struggling under oppressive regimes. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of upholding freedom and democracy wherever they are jeopardized. It mentions specific examples such as supporting the people of Ukraine in choosing their own destiny, helping displaced Syrians seek a better future, and engaging with the Cuban government on human rights. The proclamation also highlights the role of young people in calling for more government accountability and urges Americans to lead by example in promoting liberty and opportunity. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to reaffirm their commitment to freedom, dignity, and opportunity for all.